        <style>
          ######## Selectors #########
          Selector simply represents, which property corresponding to its value is going to be implements on which specific element. 
          
          Type of selectors : 

            1. Element Selector or Tag selector (element_name{})
            2. Id selector(#)
            3. Class selector(.)
            4. Universal selector(*)
            5. Grouping selector(,)
            6. Descendant selector( )
            7. Advanced selector
                a.Adjacent Sibling Selector(+)
                b.General Sibling Selector(~) 
                c.Direct Child Selector(>)
                d.Attribute Selector(element_name[type='....'])
                e.nth-of-type selector
                f.Pseudo element Selector(::)
                g.Pseudo class selector(:)
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
